    <briefdescription>
<para>User-implemented callbacks and platform hooks. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This group defines the platform abstraction points required by the ISO-TP core. Applications must provide these functions to integrate with their CAN driver, timing source, and optional debug output.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Elements in this group include:</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Debug output hook: <ref refid="group__isotp__user_1ga10a2cbca08f2a2cdb740cd4ad51358be" kindref="member">isotp_user_debug</ref>. </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>CAN transmit hook: <ref refid="group__isotp__user_1ga1443c22c029ba979ab39e47c47037f33" kindref="member">isotp_user_send_can</ref> (optionally with ISO_TP_USER_SEND_CAN_ARG). </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>Time source hook: <ref refid="group__isotp__user_1ga36dadb47afc5465d4c2fea1dedbbfcaa" kindref="member">isotp_user_get_us</ref>. </para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
